## General Design Rules
- Always prefer standard design token (for colors, spacing, typography etc.) from global CSS variables over explicit values. Maintain consistency across the design.
- Always prefer shadcn UI components over native HTML elements wherever possible (check shadcn registry and add using CLI if needed).
- When using shadcn components, Avoid overwriting default styles unless the user advises to do so.
- Avoid redundant styling tokens and tailwind classes; Optimize new components and remove unnecessary style tokens wherever possible.
- Use semantic HTML elements for layout structure wherever possible.
- Avoid hacky fixes, always try to look at the design as a whole and fix the root causes.

## React Patterns
- Implement the Headless Pattern: Extract complex interactions (keyboard nav, state) into custom hooks.
- Favor Inversion of Control: Use slots and children instead of multiple boolean props to customize UI.
- When creating custom components, follow the Compound Components pattern for modular UI sets and avoid prop-drilling.

## TailwindCSS Patterns
- Use tailwindcss @container queries for component-level responsiveness instead of viewport breakpoints.
- Use the size-x utility for square dimensions (e.g. size-4 over w-4 h-4)
- Use bg-linear-to-* instead of legacy bg-gradient-to-* syntax.
- Utilize group and peer modifiers for state-based styling instead of custom JS or nested CSS.
- Use has-[:] modifiers for complex state-based parent styling.
- Enforce aspect-ratio utilities on all dynamic media to prevent Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS).
- Move repetitive utility patterns into @layer components using @apply for high-frequency UI patterns.